Wir sind geistige und fühlende Wesen!
Das Spiegel- und Resonanzgesetz wirkt immer, auch bei dir!

Dein ganzes Leben antwortet nur auf deine geistig energetischen Gedanken und Gefühle!
Beides arbeitet total synchron. 
Häufig sind Deine Worte und Projektionen anders als Deine Gedanken und Gefühle!
-Deine Lebensumstände spiegeln alles!
BEWUSSTSEINSVERÄNDERUNGEN, jetzt in diesem Moment!

Am Ende war es der Glaube an das Nicht-gelingen in Ihr, der nicht gelöst war.
- Ihre wohlwollenden Worte waren egal, da sie im Inneren an etwas anderes glaubte und ausstrahlte. So ist das Leben!
Es antwortet permanent auf Deine ausstrahlende Energie-Glaubenssätze- und inneren Überzeugungen.

media.altText: Depression is a mood disorder that causes a persistent feeling of sadness and loss of interest.  It affects how you feel, think and behave and can lead to a variety of emotional and physical problems.  Symptoms occur most of the day, nearly every day. Symptoms include: Feelings of sadness, tearfulness, emptiness or hopelessness. Loss of interest or pleasure in most or all normal activities. Sleep disturbances, including insomnia or sleeping too much. Reduced appetite & weight loss or increased cravings/weight gain. Trouble thinking, concentrating, and remembering things. Slowed thinking, speaking or body movements. Information from: https://www.mayoclinic.org/diseases-conditions/depression/symptoms-causes/syc-20356007

yourself permeates your speech. “Sorry I'm just rambling.” “Don’t worry about it.” “Just ignore

me.” “Sorry if I’'m annoying you.” “Sorry | don’t make sense.” “Sorry about that.” Sorry, sorry, sorry. You act as if you have to beat everyone else to the punch. As if the punching bag is you. If you hate yourself first, if you hate yourself loudest, then nobody will hurt you. You clapped your hands over your ears and shut your eyes and balled yourself

up so that you’d never have to experience people’s loathing for you. And it meant you never heard their love. You drowned it out. You screamed your hatred over it. And you never got to hear it.

Common symptoms of depression: Irritability; loss of interest in work, family, or once-pleasurable activities; sleeping too much or too little; physical aches or pains; overeating or not wanting to eat at all; feeling down or hopeless.
Get support. Opening up and sharing how you are feeling can help. Togetherall is a free anonymous, online community available 24/7 where you can get (or give) support.
